10. Important Interview Questions
---------------------------------

Q1. Can unordered_multimap have duplicate keys?
Yes.

Q2. Are keys sorted?
No.

Q3. Which data structure is used?
Hash Table.

Q4. Can we use operator[]?
No.

Reason:
A key may have multiple values, so operator[]
cannot uniquely identify one mapped value.

Q5. How do we access all values of a key?

auto range = umm.equal_range(key);

Q6. How to count duplicate keys?

umm.count(key);

Q7. How to remove all values of a key?

umm.erase(key);

Q8. How to remove only one occurrence?

auto it = umm.find(key);
if(it != umm.end())
    umm.erase(it);

----------------------------------------

11. When to Use?
----------------

Use unordered_multimap when:

✓ One key maps to multiple values.
✓ Order is not important.
✓ Fast lookup is required.

Examples:

Student -> Subjects
Author -> Books
Department -> Employees
Category -> Products

----------------------------------------

12. Points to Mention in Interview
----------------------------------

✓ Hash Table based container.
✓ Stores key-value pairs.
✓ Duplicate keys are allowed.
✓ Keys are NOT ordered.
✓ Average O(1) operations.
✓ operator[] is NOT available.
✓ equal_range() retrieves all values for a key.
✓ erase(key) removes ALL elements with that key.
✓ erase(iterator) removes ONE element.
✓ lower_bound()/upper_bound() are NOT available.
